<p align="center"> Welcome to Yayger's House -O- Pain!</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleolanhazzan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leolan Hazzan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><FONT COLOR=AA0000><B>Lanys.com Moderator</B></FONT></span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 3:37:34 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.acinternet.com/leolan/leopic.asp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire: Lets make some rules.</span><hr size=1> And be prepared for non-clerics to fight for Ragefire as well.<br>
<br>
Setting up for him shouldn't take more than 30-45 mins really (assuming giants are dead).  Everyone knows that it's hotly contested and they need to move fast.  Nor does it take more than 3-4 groups to put him down easy. <p>&nbsp;- Leo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>h0x0r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/6/01 5:02:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire: Lets make some rules.</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>
&quot;why make rules for decent clerics to follow when others will simply steamroll them?&quot; - Yayger<br>
<br>
Why not try to make those rules anyway? Luclin did and it is working (at least, at the moment). Why give in and let the greed mob force everyone to act the same way? Being honourable is sometimes its own reward, I would say. And the reputation of those who don't give a *^&amp;%$ for others is not going to get any better, now, is it? Personally, if I have to steal the camp by force from anyone else in a rude and aggressive manner to be able to complete this (or any) quest, I would not want to complete it at all, my dignity is worth more to me than that. And I am pretty sure this is the case for most players.<br>
